        <p>
            DataAnnotations is used to configure your model classes, 
            which will highlight the most commonly needed configurations. 
            DataAnnotations are also understood by a number of .NET applications, 
            such as ASP.NET MVC, which allows these applications to leverage 
            the same annotations for client-side validations. DataAnnotation 
            attributes override default Code-First conventions.
        </p>
